column5: It didn't work perfectly but it worked. The child is safe and those alert Cops should praised not investigated.   http://www.msn.com/en-ca/news/canada/amber-alert-case-being-reviewed-after-chase-crash-near-pembroke/ar-BBrUjhe?ocid=spartandhp

How much danger was her life in? That's a vital question in a case like this.. the girls family was pleading for him not to harm her so they must have known something bad could happen.. and when "authorities" say non life threatening injuries that doesn't mean she won't be permanently disabled from this...
